Subject: [PATCH] Update manpage for -I and -O

Signed-off-by: Osamu Aoki <osamu@debian.org>
---
 man/unzip.1 | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/man/unzip.1 b/man/unzip.1
index 75a7060..f7d1685 100644
--- a/man/unzip.1
+++ b/man/unzip.1
@@ -545,6 +545,10 @@ names.  The default is to exploit the destination file system, preserving
 case and extended file name characters on an ODS5 destination file system;
 and applying the ODS2-compatibility file name filtering on an ODS2 destination
 file system.
+.IP \fB\-O\fP\ \fIcharset\fP
+specify a character encoding for DOS, Windows and OS/2 archives
+.IP \fB\-I\fP\ \fIcharset\fP
+specify a character encoding for UNIX and otherarchives
 .PD
 .\" =========================================================================
 .SH "ENVIRONMENT OPTIONS"
@@ -798,6 +802,14 @@ or
 unzip \-l\-\-q file.zip
 .EE
 \fR(Extra minuses in options don't hurt.)
+.PP
+To extract Japanese archive with sjis encoded filenames on Debian GNU/Linux:
+.PP
+.EX
+unzip \-Osjis file.zip
+.EE
+.PP
+(List of usable \fIcharset\fP is available by executing \fCiconv \-\-list\fR.)
 .PD
 .\" =========================================================================
 .SH TIPS
